Class SpectrogramMeasurement

  • java.lang.Object
    • lusc.net.github.SpectrogramMeasurement

  • public class SpectrogramMeasurement
extends java.lang.Object
    This Class measures elements within spectrograms - measuring a range of acoustic parameters It interacts closely with the Song class.

    Rob

      • getSignal

        public java.util.LinkedList<int[][]> getSignal(int[][] pointList,
                                      int unx)
        This method uses a hysteresis loop method to search for a signal within a highlighted region of a spectrogram
        Parameters:
        pointList - a highlighted region of the spectrogram. Lists min and max freqs for a range of times
        unx - length of the spectrogram (shouldn't be necessary!)
        Returns:
        a LinkedList of int[][] containing signal locations

      • merge

        public void merge(int p,
         SpectrPane sp,
         int currentMinX)
        This method attempts to merge two measured elements into one - based on a user decision to do so. This is currently a bit buggy, and needs some investigation
        Parameters:
        p - the index of the first element to merge in the eleList
        sp - the SpectrPane object that called merge
        currentMinX - current minimum time on the spectrogram

      • measureAndAddElements

        public int measureAndAddElements(java.util.LinkedList<int[][]> signals,
                        SpectrPane sp,
                        int currentMinX)
        This is the organizing method for measuring acoustic parameters of new elements, and constructing new Element objects from the measurements.
        Parameters:
        signals - a list of new elements, described by their locations on the spectrograms
        sp - the SpectrPane object that called this
        currentMinX - current minimum time value of the spectrogram.
        Returns:
        an int containing the number of added elements

        Parameters:

        results - LinkedList into which to insert the results
